Pakistan is likely to produce a record7.6 mln bales (375 lbs each) of cotton from the current 1986/87crop, exceeding a target of 7.2 mln bales, Food and AgricultureMinister Mohammad Ibrahim Baluch said.    He told a Pakistan Central Cotton Committee meeting herethe present was the third consecutive poroductionrecord-setting year and said the momentum would be acceleratedin the future, the official APP news agency reported.    Baluch said indications were that Pakistan is to attain arecord cotton production of 7.6 mln bales, compared to the1985/86 crop of 7.2 mln bales which also represented the targetearlier set by authorities for this year's production. Reuter&#3;